-- Colombia congress passes reform extending, modifying taxes
-- By Carlos Vargas
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 07:18PM EST
-- None



BOGOTA, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Colombia's lower house approved a tax reform on Monday that will enable the government to raise 53 trillion pesos ($22.3 billion) over the next four years, by extending and modifying a number of existing taxes due to expire at the end of the year.      (Reporting by Carlos Vargas; Writing by Peter Murphy and Julia Symmes Cobb; Editing by Lisa Shumaker)  ((Peter.Murphy@thomsonreuters.com; +57 1 634 4133; Reuters Messaging: peter.murphy.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: COLOMBIA TAX/

